<item>
            <title>[LU-17003] DNE system doesn&apos;t need to support REP-ACK</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17003</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;DNE system doesn&apos;t need to support REP-ACK, because similar to the original Commit-on-Sharing, EX|PW mode locks are downgraded to TXN mode, and kept in reply_state till transaction commit, which can guarantee transaction dependency.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
